Class BasePublisher

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cesecore.internal.UpgradeableDataHashMap

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, IUpgradeableData, FullEntityPublisher

    CustomPublisherContainer, LdapPublisher, MultiGroupPublisher
    public abstract class BasePublisher
extends UpgradeableDataHashMap
implements Serializable, Cloneable, FullEntityPublisher
    BasePublisher is a basic class that should be inherited by all types of publishers in the system.

        revocationReason - reason
        Returns:
        true if the certificate should be published.

      • storeCertificate

        public abstract boolean storeCertificate​(AuthenticationToken admin,
                                         Certificate incert,
                                         String username,
                                         String password,
                                         String userDN,
                                         String cafp,
                                         int status,
                                         int type,
                                         long revocationDate,
                                         int revocationReason,
                                         String tag,
                                         int certificateProfileId,
                                         long lastUpdate,
                                         ExtendedInformation extendedinformation)
                                  throws PublisherException
        Publishes a certificate to a certificate store. If status is not active for the certificate, the publisher may choose to not publish the certificate, for instance if revoke removes a certificate from LDAP, re-publishing the certificate should not add it again if the status is revoked. To revoke a certificate (already revoked by the CA) call with status=CertificateDataBean.CERT_ACTIVE, the Publisher decides what to do, if anything.
        Parameters:
        admin - admin
        incert - The certificate to be stored.
        username - Username of end entity owning the certificate.
        password - Password given to the user, may be null if no password exists for the user.
        userDN - if a DN object is not found in the certificate use object from user data instead, can be null.
        cafp - Fingerprint (hex) of the CAs certificate.
        status - Status of the certificate (from CertificateDataBean.CERT_ACTIVE, CERT_REVOKED etc).
        type - Type of certificate (from CertificateDataBean.CERTTYPE_ENDENTITY etc).
        revocationDate - Date for revocation (of revoked), like System.currentTimeMillis(), or -1 if not revoked.
        revocationReason - reason for revocation from RevokedCertInfo, RevokedCertInfo.NOT_REVOKED if not revoked.
        tag - TAg
        certificateProfileId - Profile
        lastUpdate - Date
        extendedinformation - contains extended information about the user, like picture, is null if no extendedinformation exists about the user.
        Returns:
        true if storage was successful.
        Throws:
        PublisherException - if a communication or other error occurs.

                                CertificateData certificateData,

      • storeCertificate

        public boolean storeCertificate​(AuthenticationToken authenticationToken,
                                CertificateData certificateData,
                                Base64CertData base64CertData,
                                String password,
                                String userDN,
                                ExtendedInformation extendedinformation)
                         throws PublisherException
        Variation of the storeCertificate method which gets the full information needed to call either of the other storeCertificate methods. This is needed for MultiGroupPublisher for example, which can call publishers of either type.
        Parameters:
        authenticationToken - token
        certificateData - data
        base64CertData - cert data
        password - pwd
        userDN - DN
        extendedinformation - Info
        Returns:
        true if storage was successful.
        Throws:
        PublisherException - if a communication or other error occurs.
        See Also:
        storeCertificate(AuthenticationToken, Certificate, String, String, String, String, int, int, long, int, String, int, long, ExtendedInformation), storeCertificate(AuthenticationToken, CertificateData, Base64CertData)
